robots.txt  -  reaching disallowed pages
cookies and user roles  -  mostly hidden
X-Original-URL and X-Rewrite-URL  - used to override the URL in the original request, tell the front-end from which page we arrived
X-Forwarded-For  -  header that tells the server from which IP the request arrived, we use that header for IP spoofing 
GET/POST  -  changing the request method
multi-step processes  -  Sometimes, a website will implement rigorous access controls over some of these steps, but ignore others. 
Referer-based  -  for sub-pages such as /admin/deleteUser only inspects the Referer header. 
